{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"15b67879-c0c1-4455-a71d-fcdd38cc56f9","content":"Good news — with .NET 10 SDK, `dotnet test` **natively uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform** when it detects an MTP-enabled project (like yours with `EnableMSTestRunner`). The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property is **no longer needed** and can be removed.\n\nHere's the change:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_011abS1VR6nV5PbTDvij6APq","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing obsolete MTP property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01KeKQYSHeJF9ML4tEJbpjJx","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-56fd0140b9e74ea280e22bcedfcfe5ca/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-56fd0140b9e74ea280e22bcedfcfe5ca/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"f0535af3-ebd0-47c6-aec9-abb71efda87d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK (10.0.100) and is using MSTest with `EnableMSTestRunner` and `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` set to true.\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) without needing the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property. Starting with .NET 10 SDK, `dotnet test` uses MTP by default when the test project is an MTP-based project (i.e., has `EnableMSTestRunner` or uses `Microsoft.Testing.Platform`).\n\n\nSince .NET 10 SDK handles MTP natively, the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property can be safely removed from the project configuration.","outputTokens":501,"requestId":"7C19:175BE3:2686147:2AA40A1:69F94139"},"id":"b3fcfa49-4588-4332-9db1-f2a4616cf7dd","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:00:49.743Z","parentId":"83190411-e94e-4778-a65f-362b5284a63b"}
